		  <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;"><a href="/profile/Yukariki">Yukariki</a> <small><span style="font-weight: normal;"> | 02-12-14, 5:41 AM</span></small></div>
		  On credit: Since I work for various fan translators and I myself know how boring and terrible translation can be, I like to give them credit whenever I can. Yes, it's volunteer work. But I react the same way I see high school and college students taking out our trash every afternoon: I give them a smile and talk to them. People volunteer for work like this not just because they like it, they want to feel like they're contributing to someone. It's that kind of dedication that makes translation possible and worthy enough to exist.<br />
<br />
Translators, even the official ones, are very unloved. I wonder who knows Jay Rubin. And if people actually know Haruki Murakami translates stuff. Make their day brighter.</td>
